				.text-18-col
					.text-18-content.content
						p But yesterday night, GMT+1, something beautiful happened. Something that shook my spirit and body and made another travel, a previous travel, emerge, come back to life. I got a comment from Abraham, Venice Beach, Los Angeles that stranger, whom I had met just for a few minutes five years ago, whose aura had impressed me, and about whom I had finally written a story, was getting back to me.
						p I went through a rollercoaster of contradictory emotions: skepticism, realization, happiness, guilt, elation, excitement, curiosity. I remember you, Abraham. Vividly. I remember your eyes and your hand shaking mine. I thought I had grasped at least a bit of who you were; enough to write an article about “all the rest”: the “you” that I had never got to know.
					.text-18-quote
